  "title": ".Net Developer",
  "description": "<p><strong>.Net Software Developer - Singapore</strong><br />We are currently looking for <strong>.NET Software Engineers</strong> with <strong>3+ years of hands-on experience in C# .NET</strong> to join a team focused on <strong>refactoring and modernising legacy software</strong> and leveraging <strong>GenAI technologies.</strong><br />This is a great opportunity to work on <strong>digital transformation projects.</strong><br /><strong>What's in it for you:</strong></p><ul><li>Enterprise Level Systems</li><li>Excellent Career Progression Opportunities</li><li>Built-from-Scratch environment on In-house applications</li><li>Up to 1 month completion bonus every year</li><li>Location: Centre of Singapore</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Develop, enhance and maintain the existing enterprise-level system.</li><li>Investigate and resolve software defects in existing C# .NET, MS SQL, JAVA applications.</li><li>Perform detailed <strong>root cause analysis</strong> for reported issues and propose sustainable solutions.</li><li>Collaborate with QA and business teams to <strong>reproduce bugs</strong> and verify fixes.</li><li>Write and maintain <strong>unit tests and regression tests</strong> using frameworks such as MSTest, NUnit, or xUnit.</li><li>Optimize and refactor code for improved performance and maintainability.</li><li>Review logs and metrics to diagnose system behavior and recommend improvements.</li><li>Work closely with team members to ensure timely delivery of fixes and patches.</li><li>Document resolutions and updates in internal knowledge bases.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>At least 2 years of experience</strong> in <strong>C# .NET </strong>software development with exposure to Java.</li><li>At least 4 years of experience in <strong>MS SQL Server</strong> and writing/debugging SQL queries.</li><li>Experienced in performing root cause analysis and resolving performance issues.</li><li>Familiarity with <strong>CI/CD pipelines</strong> (e.g., Jenkins, Azure DevOps, Git).</li><li>Exposure to Microservices / Kafka</li><li>Experience with <strong>Visual Studio</strong>, <strong>Git</strong>, and <strong>issue tracking tools</strong> like JIRA.</li><li>Experience working on large-scale enterprise applications.</li><li>Excellent analytical and troubleshooting skills</li><li>Strong communication and collaboration abilities with proactive mindset.</li></ul><p>This is a 1 year contract to start, renewable and convertible to permanent.</p>",
